  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 190&deg;C/ 170&deg;C (fan)/ 375&deg;F/ Gas 5</p>\r\n<p>Peel, top and tail&nbsp;and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;finely</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>celery</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Peel and chop the<strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"text-highlight\">brown</span> onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>finely&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>beef mince</strong>, breaking it up as you go and cook for 2-3 min, until starting to brown&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced carrot</strong>, <strong>chopped celery</strong> and <strong>chopped onion</strong> to the browned mince and cook for 5 min or until the vegetables have slightly softened</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">,&nbsp;add</span> the <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>dried dill</strong>, <strong>Henderson's <span class=\"text-highlight\">R</span>elish</strong>&nbsp;&amp; half of the <strong>dried oregano</strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"text-highlight\">&ndash;</span> this is your<strong> stock mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/447_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir&nbsp;1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>flour</strong> and half of the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later) into the mince&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>stock mixture</strong>, mix well and season with plenty of <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 10 min, until most of the liquid has absorbed <span class=\"text-highlight\">&ndash;</span> this is your <strong>beef mixture</strong></p>",
